      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "Here are more tests.\r\nOS X 10.11.6 (15G22010) + 0.17.0 (Qt 5.9.6)\r\n\r\nStep 1: Dock menu \"Hide\"\r\n\r\n... some variants of...\r\nStep 2: Dock menu \"Show\" - works as expected: shows main window and brings it to the front.\r\n\r\nStep 2: Dock menu \"Send\" or \"Receive\" - _does not work_: does not show main window at all.\r\n\r\nStep 2: Dock menu \"Sign message...\" or \"Verify message...\" - works with some issues: (a) shows main window, (b) shows \"sign/verify\" window, (c) _does not_ bring any of mentioned windows to the front, (d) makes app icon bounce continuously :) , (e) many items of the Dock menu get greyed.\r\n\r\nStep 2: Dock menu \"Debug window\" - works as expected: shows both main window and debug window, and brings the latter to the front.\r\n\r\nMoreover, using Command-H or \"Hide Bitcoin Core\" from the app menu in the Step 1 does not change behaviour.\r\n\r\nUPDATE: also tested on macOS 10.13.6 (17G65) + 0.17.0 (Qt 5.9.6)\r\nResults are the same.",
